<h1>Trusted Certificate Authorities</h1>

<p>A proper identity matching or UDAP client must obtain a private key and certificate from an authority. Then UDAP resource servers and patient matching servers
will allow the clients access if the server providers trust the certificate authority.</p>

<table id="authorities" class="table">
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Created</th>
    <th>Certificate</th>
    <th colspan="2">Actions</th>
  </tr>
  <% @authorities.each do |authority| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= authority.name %></td>
    <td><%= authority.created_at.strftime '%r %x' %></td>
    <td><%= link_to "Download PEM", authority, download: authority.name.parameterize + ".pem" %></td>
    <td><%= link_to "Edit", edit_authority_path(authority), class: "text-success" %></td>
    <td><%= button_to "Delete", authority, data: {'turbo-method' => :delete}, class: "btn btn-sm btn-danger" %></td>
  </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<%= link_to "New authority", new_authority_path, class: "btn btn-primary" %>
